I'm from Bihar. I can understand the meaning... I have gone through this, how it feels when you see an other Bihari pretending like he's from some other place and feels shame of his own identity. 
How they never learn  their state's language. 
And proudly say "Mujhe nahi pasnd bihari, mjhe aati v nahi hai". 

I guess it's the condition of many people who feel shame of their identity despite being bihari or punjabi.
